Let $\{x_t\}_{t\in\mathbb Z}$ be a $d$-dimensional stochastic process generated by a vector autoregressive moving average (VARMA) model
\begin{equation} \label{eqn:arma}
\phi_0(L) x_t = \theta_0(L) \varepsilon_t,
\end{equation}
where $\phi_0(L)$ and $\theta_0(L)$ are lag polynomials with orders $p$ and $q$ and $\varepsilon_t$ is a $d$-dimensional innovation vector with a non-zero mean representing the contamination bias.

